<dl id="n03008g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03008g">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03008g"> 8(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>6yrs<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> Antrim ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> <mark>After six years&apos; captivity</mark> Patrick escaped from Ireland to France and made his way to Tours, where he stayed for four years receiving instructions from St. Martin. Then he spent about fourteen years with St. Germanus of Auxerre, who sent him to Pope Celestine to receive the episcopacy. <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 11</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Continued on next page.</mm> </dd></dl>
